\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where
\lang english

\begin_inset Formula $Y_{h}$
\end_inset


\lang american
 denotes the outcome of interest for household h measured alternatively as maize productivity,
 gross income from maize and adoption of hybrid seeds.
 While previous studies model productivity outcomes in logarithmic form (Udry,
 1996),
 we employ the inverse hyperbolic sine transformation to accommodate zero productivity and income observations:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
ainh(Y)=ln(Y+\sqrt{Y^{2}+1})\label{eq:one-1-3}
\end{equation}

