\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When considering the adoption of hybrid seed as an outcome variable,
 the OLS specification corresponds to a Linear Probability Model (LPM).
 While nonlinear models such as logit or probit are often used for binary outcomes,
 the LPM provides a straightforward interpretation and facilitates comparison with the continuous outcomes analyzed in this study.
 However,
 the LPM has some limitations.
 The main disadvantage is that the predicted value could fall outside the zero-to-one probability values (Gujarati,
 2021).
 Robustness checks using logit specifications that follow logistic cumulative distribution are reported in the Appendix and present similar results.
