 Maybe Add:
 Since the gap is defined as male minus female,
 positive values indicate higher average productivity or income among male-headed households relative to female-headed households.
 Reversing the order of the groups would produce the same magnitude with the opposite sign
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Equation (1) relies on the restrictive assumption that the returns to observable characteristics are identical for male and female headed households.
 To relax this assumption,
 we follow standard practice in the literature and estimate separate linear regressions for each group.
 The expected outcome of the gender-specific regressions can be written as:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
E(Y_{m})=\bar{X}_{m}\hat{\beta}_{m})\label{eq:one-1-1-1}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
E(Y_{f})=\bar{X}_{f}\hat{\beta}_{f})\label{eq:one-1-1-2}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\lang american
Where 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{m}$
\end_inset


\family roman
