\begin_layout Plain Layout
The study advances the literature by giving new context-specific evidence on potential gender-differentiated outcomes in smallholder maize farming,
 with particular attention to the role of hybrid seed varieties adoption as a key driver of agricultural performance.
 The findings have policy implications for equitable productivity and income outcomes in maize production in Eastern Uganda.
